pr_review_comment_body:
Rather than testing `sys.version_info`, this is probably better as a conditional import:

```python
        try:
            from types import ClassType
        except ImportError:
            pass
        else:
            assert not isinstance(C, (type, ClassType))

```

@matthayes mentioned required keyword args. It looks like this is only 3.0 compatible [PEP-3102](http://legacy.python.org/dev/peps/pep-3102/). Based on @ewencp's comment below, I still think:

    produce(*args, **kwargs)

Is the best we can do right now.
